I think Mike Joy did a great job defending the decision
on Wind Tunnel tonight--along with some great footage
that shows that it's not clear who would have won
if the yellow flag had been thrown between the time
that KyBu fishtailed and the time that KH &amp; MM
crossed the line.  Most of that time, KH was in
front of MM.

Joy's analysis:

1. No wrecks would have been stopped by throwing the
flag.

2. By not throwing the flag, NASCAR let MM &amp; KH settle
the Big Question by racing.

3. No one in the wreck was endangered by the race between
MM &amp; KH.

Not covered: was not throwing the flag unfair to the rest
of the field.  Lots of folks got passed (eg Blaney in the
07) who would not have been passed under the normal
"instant yellow" rules.

On balance, I think NASCAR made the right call.

Marty
