caution flag on the last two laps."

They also said (at one point) that there were three
laps left.  They really meant two, and kind of corrected
the error within a minute or so.

There are three final flags but only two laps:

Green: one lap.

White: one lap.

Checkered: race over.

It seems to me on my mental replay tape that I can hear
the talent (Mike Joy?  Well, it's his voice in my head.)
saying: "If a caution comes out during the overtime, the
race will end under caution."

