Yes this is the procedure that they will follow. Because this crash happened
in the tri-oval I can tell you that nothing would have changed except
'maybe' the scoring and even then, MM may not have been the leader at the
moment the yellow was shown. It does take a few seconds for that to happen.
Also, what if KH had been ruled ahead at the time the yellow actually came
out, i.e. the lights changed to yellow, and MM would have been the leader
when they crossed the line? The hue and cry from the fans would have been,
and rightfully so, thunderous. From someone who has been in this position a
number of times as the flagman and race director responsible for calling the
yellow flag, I would have and have done the same thing that NASCAR did, let
the leaders finish under green. Nobody, and I mean nobody would have been
spared in that crash because they simply would not have been able to react
getting the yellow light out and then the drivers and spotters communicating
with the drivers, able to slow down or even react to avoid crashing. It was
a great call on NASCAR's behalf.
